Systems Analyst. #NASASocial alum. Exploring the digital life. Fan of the Padres, Seahawks and craft beer.


Scott Kingery
scott@techlifeweb.com,
San Diego
California
United States
(858) 324-4859
Google+
@techlifeweb
LinkedIn
Facebook

Since the early days of the personal computer, the days of the TRS-80, I have been interested in computers and electronics. Currently I am a systems analyst and manage Documentum systems. I used to do a bit of Lotus Notes development but lately I have been developing databases in Quickbase.

I am into just about everything you can do with a PC including digital photography, networking, video and blogging. I enjoy the challenge of trying to figure out how to do something and build knowledge around that. I like writing how-to’s for the things I learn and you’ll see some of those from time to time. I also enjoy traveling and have been to most of the 50 US States including Alaska and Hawaii. I think there are 4 or 5 I still need to get to.
